  "label": "Canvas-Screened Alcove",
  "description": "This narrow bedroom occupies a recessed alcove cut into Cindervale’s reused ashlar, its old stone faces darkened by soot and lime dust. A canvas screen hangs from an iron rod to divide the sleeping space from the hearthroom, stained by coal-smoke and stiffened with age. A low pallet and a battered chest sit beneath a slit-high vent that admits little light and less air. The surrounding masonry carries sound cleanly, and the iron straps embedded in the wall reinforce the sense of a residence built for siege and ordinance.",
